Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: reprounzip-vagrant
Version: 0.2
Summary: Allows the ReproZip unpacker to create virtual machines
Home-page: http://github.com/remram44/reprozip
Author: Remi Rampin
Author-email: remirampin@gmail.com
License: BSD
Description: Plugin for ReproZip adding Vagrant support to the unpacker.
        
        This requires reprounzip. It adds the 'reprounzip vagrant' subcommand which
        builds a virtual machine template from a packed experiment, allowing to run it
        on a different system/architecture (notably on Windows). You will need Vagrant
        to run this virtual machine template.
        
Keywords: reprozip,reprounzip,reproducibility,provenance
Platform: UNKNOWN
